**Abstract:**
Personal statement dated January 3, 1998 titled "1998: State of My Project" outlining the book project's aims. Diagnoses Catholic intellectual tradition as tainted by intellectualism-rationalism that harms Christian self-understanding. Argues post-modernism brought this tradition to halt but offered no alternative. Articulates key insight: after giving up contemplative truth, what remains is Christian faith by which we are saved. Acknowledges this position looks like fideism but argues the accusation depends on staying within the old paradigm.

**AI Recommendation:** Key autobiographical statement; see 98-JAN-1 variant.

